<subSubSection pageId="80" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="80.[151,1436,151,766]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,703,729]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerstmeier &amp; Eberle" authorityYear="2010" box="[605,677,704,729]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Xenorthrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubris">
<emphasis box="[605,677,704,729]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">rubris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a Latin adjective meaning ruby, refers to the coloration of the elytra.
</paragraph>
